column5: Joey, my Wife and I slogged it out on a slushy, stocked back lake. We all got wet and cold. Luckily I brought the 2-man eskimo and propane heater, so she stayed warm and happy.  After a couple dozen 3" perch, the tiny jigging rap I was using to cause a perch-rucus ended up calling in a nice Rainbow!  I was a happy customer, especially given my poor record for inland rainbows.
The fishing reports are really flowing now.  That's a solid bow Chad, nice going!
Way to go Chad, definitely a nice bow!  Good idea to keep wifey warm - or you'll be cold tonight!  LOL!
Your efforts paid off nice Rainbow.
Nothing wrong with getting cold and wet as long as you are rewarded with a fish!!
Nice Rainbow! Very cool, must of been nice little fight.
It was a great fight.! Thanks guys
A pretty pretty bow that is.  Nice!
Really enjoying all the reports the last few days.  Nice fish Chad.
Really enjoying all the reports the last few days.  Nice fish Chad.  You just needed to make the request for them apparently to get them all flowing in.  Great fish Chad  and report
